b'We serve the public conversation.'
b'We have to talk. \nAnd listen.'
b'Every expression adds to a layer. \nThe layer is a conversation.\nThe conversation is humanity.'

b"Let's talk about what matters. 
Let's have fun.
Let's evolve and change. 
Positively.
Let's argue. 
Productively."
b'Talk can turn into action. \nCollaboration.\nHow?'
b'Everything is connected.'

b'People talk about what they care about. 
Faith.
Food.
Water.
Shelter. 
Safety. 
Family. 
Health. 
Work. 
Money. 
Belonging. 
Fun. 
Friends. 
Status. 
Respect. 
Love.'

b"One nation will not improve our global condition. 
We'll all do that.
Together.
Conversation doesn't see borders.
It's porous."

b"What's true?
We're human.
Our bodies are similar.
We get the same ailments.
We live on the same planet.
We share so much.
We are more same than different. 
Conversation reveals this truth."

b'What is the public conversation? 
Is it about something we all share? 
Climate?
AI?
Religious tolerance?
Race, nationality, gender?'
